h(x) = \ln(x^4)
\Rightarrow \ln(x^4) = mx = 4
  \begin{align} h'(x) = m &\Rightarrow 4/x = m  \\ &\Rightarrow x = 4/m \\ &\Rightarrow t(x) = \frac{4x}{e} \end{align} 
